                Induction ranges use electromagnetic fields to heat cookware
                directly, offering precise temperature control and energy
                efficiency. However, they can encounter problems such as
                malfunctioning induction coils, faulty control panels, and
                issues with the sensors. Professional repair services are
                essential for diagnosing and fixing these specialized issues.
                Technicians may need to replace induction coils, repair control
                panels, or address sensor malfunctions. Repair costs for
                induction ranges generally range from <b>$200 to $450</b>. Given
                the advanced technology involved, regular maintenance by
                factory-trained technicians is recommended to keep the appliance
                running smoothly and efficiently.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content__page-desc">
